{"id":541372570,"lang":"python3","time":"11 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1629451435,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"92 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/541372570/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Valid Sudoku","memory":"14.4 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def isValidSudoku(self, board: List[List[str]]) -> bool:\n        #checking if 1D array valid\n        def valid(arr):\n            seen = set()\n            for val in arr:\n                if val == '.':\n                    continue\n                if val in seen:\n                    return False\n                seen.add(val)\n            return True\n        \n        #Row wise\n        for row in board:\n            if not valid(row):\n                return False\n        \n        #column wise\n        for j in range(9):\n            col = [board[i][j] for i in range(9)]\n            if not valid(col):\n                return False\n       #Block wise\n        for i in range(0, 9, 3):\n            for j in range(0, 9, 3):\n                block = [board[k][l] for k in range(i, i+3) for l in range(j, j+3)]\n                if not valid(block):\n                    return False\n        return True","compare_result":"","title_slug":"valid-sudoku"}
